ant"},{"source":"recbGb0Cb2yIRqmle","target":"recFqCoLVEfASibXd","label":"participant"},{"source":"recpCMN0bRpzByjaR","target":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","label":"event"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recFAk8M3Dk8tn9Xo","label":"participant"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"reclOIbdzOMEvWssM","label":"participant"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recgkzNX07a7kGFYL","label":"participant"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recFqCoLVEfASibXd","label":"participant"},{"source":"recpCMN0bRpzByjaR","target":"recAIElabptRPkpxz","label":"event"},{"source":"recAIElabptRPkpxz","target":"recgkzNX07a7kGFYL","label":"participant"},{"source":"recAIElabptRPkpxz","target":"recFqCoLVEfASibXd","label":"participant"},{"source":"recAIElabptRPkpxz","target":"recFAk8M3Dk8tn9Xo","label":"participant"},{"source":"recAIElabptRPkpxz","target":"reclOIbdzOMEvWssM","label":"participant"}],"verses":[{"id":"recb92pQdP7c8RL07","ref":"Acts.2.9","text":"Parthians, and Medes, and Elamites, and the dwellers in Mesopotamia, and in Judaea, and Cappadocia, in Pontus, and Asia,","year":33},{"id":"rec8XIlMj4T6GNIn4","ref":"Acts.6.9","text":"Then there arose certain of the synagogue, which is called the synagogue of the Libertines, and Cyrenians, and Alexandrians, and of them of Cilicia and of Asia, disputing with Stephen.","year":33},{"id":"recxipFQsVXMzs9XY","ref":"Acts.16.6","text":"Now when they had gone throughout Phrygia and the region of Galatia, and were forbidden of the Holy Ghost to preach the word in Asia,","year":53},{"id":"recHI4SYqq6s4J0Zj","ref":"Acts.19.10","text":"And this continued by the space of two years; so that all they which dwelt in Asia heard the word of the Lord Jesus, both Jews and Greeks.","year":58},{"id":"rec5IApHnPQHLxg9h","ref":"Acts.19.22","text":"So he sent into Macedonia two of them that ministered unto him, Timotheus and Erastus; but he himself stayed in Asia for a season.","year":58},{"id":"recJnb6YnwpOYBErv","ref":"Acts.19.26","text":"Moreover ye see and hear, that not alone at Ephesus, but almost throughout all Asia, this Paul hath persuaded and turned away much people, saying that they be no gods, which are made with hands:","year":58},{"id":"recdnRcnkXBdlJEhL","ref":"Acts.19.27","text":"So that not only this our craft is in danger to be set at nought; but also that the temple of the great goddess Diana should be despised, and her magnificence should be destroyed, whom all Asia and the world worshippeth.","year":58},{"id":"rec9QF9UZ901OZwCB","ref":"Acts.20.16","text":"For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus, because he would not spend the time in Asia: for he hasted, if it were possible for him, to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost.","year":60}]}
